50|$|The gradual darkening of the ink {{is due to}} the {{oxidation}} of {{the iron}} ions from ferrous (Fe2+) to ferric (Fe3+) state by atmospheric oxygen. (For that reason, the liquid ink had to be stored in a <b>well-stoppered</b> <b>bottle,</b> and often became unusable after a time.) The ferric ions react with the tannic acid or some derived compound (possibly gallic acid or pyrogallol) to form a polymeric organometallic compound.|$|E

